post_text: Today!
shared_text:
Sangamon Valley PTO
August 10 at 8:38 AM ·

In-Person Registration this THURSDAY!

Registration will be Thursday, August 13 at the Niantic Methodist Church from 11:00 AM to 7:00 PM. Any new students to the district MUST register in person. Any family wishing to register in person will do so at the church due to the ongoing construction at our school campuses. The following is a list of safety precautions that will be implemented for the protection of everyone:

Parking is available on the east and south sides of the Church. Everyone will enter the building from the west side (Pritchett Street) and exit out the east side.

Masks must be worn to enter the building and remain on at all times.

If possible, please do not bring children to registration.

Only 20 people will be allowed in the building at a time.

Registration forms may be picked up at the entrance and filled out prior to entry.

Social distancing must be maintained at all times.

To avoid lines and long waits, please register online.

Please check your email for a survey from Superintendent Meadows!

This survey will be used to assist SV in determining the best course of action for returning to school in the fall. We are currently planning multiple scenarios for learning and will continue to analyze each scenario based on safety guidelines. Your feedback about your comfort level, safety precautions, learning options, and other topics is greatly appreciated. Please complete and return this survey, one per household, no later than 12:00 pm on July 13, 2020.



https://forms.gle/2E2VAX8dX7wFo43u7



Thank you,

Mr. Robert Meadows
Superintendent

July 10 at 8:18 AM ·

Important Preschool Screening Update!

Kindergarten students will NOT need to be screened this year. Please attend the August 13th registration day (more information to come)

Preschool screening will be August 31st-Sept 2nd. Students must be 3 years of age or older on or before Sept 1, 2020 in order to be eligible to qualify for the pre-k program. Mrs. Allen will contact those who signed up for screenings in March to schedule an appointment. If you did not sign up for March screenings please call the SVP office the week of August 24th.

shared_text:
Sangamon Valley Intermediate School
April 21 at 5:23 PM ·

Dear students and families,
Good afternoon! This is a follow-up to the email that you received earlier today from Mr. Meadows. I think many of us expected schools to remain closed, but it was still difficult to receive the news from the Governor last Friday.
It has been incredibly rewarding to work with a staff that has adjusted to the new demands of remote learning and staying connected to our students. We will continue to do our best to support the students and families of this school community.
Attached is information regarding the end of the year. Please read it carefully and let me know if you have any questions. Please continue to communicate with your child's teacher and stay safe and healthy. We miss you and look forward to having students in our school once again!

Brian Britton

Sangamon Valley School District #9 Food Service Emergency Order Form *Updated 3/31/2020*

Sangamon Valley School District Food Service
April 1 at 1:22 PM ·

***UPDATE***

For the safety of our volunteer employees and our Sangamon Valley Families, we will be making some changes to our Food Service Distribution.

There will only be ONE PICK-UP DAY. When you pick up
on MONDAYS, between 9:00-11:00, you will receive a
weeks worth of breakfast and lunches in each bag.

There will be only ONE PICK-UP LOCATION (Sangamon Valley High School in Niantic). The pick-up is located in the shop on the south end of the building by the garage door. Please pull around by the door and remain in your vehicle.

You MUST fill out a NEW form to receive meals from this point forward. Also, if you sign up for meals, please pick them up! We have dedicated employees volunteering their time to make sure our students do not go hungry!

The deadline to sign up for meals is Thursday, April 2nd at 12:00 p.m. This will allow us time to make sure we have the necessary items for each meal. No additional signups will be allowed!!

https://forms.gle/FEGi6LZUcRwPDmVe7

post_text: This is awesome!
shared_text:
McAlister's Deli (Forsyth, IL)
March 14 at 1:52 PM ·

Dear friends,
As we all know, Illinois has closed schools temporarily in an attempt to control the spread of COVID 19. We believe this is the right decision, but also understand that it may present challenges to families in the communities we serve. We'd like to help.

If you are concerned about ensuring your children have a hearty lunch, stop by McAlister's Deli from 11am - 1pm, Monday through Friday. Every kid can receive a free sack lunch that contains a turkey and cheese sandwich, chips, applesauce and a cookie. Completely free, no other purchase is necessary.

We want to do our part to make sure our friends get through this challenging time. So take this worry off your plate, and put it on ours. We will get through it. Together.

Your McAlister's Deli TEAm

#preparednotscared #nohungrykids

PS - Kids aged 12 and under also eat free every Monday evening from 5pm - close when their parents dine in.
